    "During preference optimization, we then optimize both the preference optimization loss (e.g., L DPO) and the regularization loss (L reg).",
    "The preference optimization loss aims to increase the margin between the probabilities of preferred and dispreferred sequences, while the regularization loss maximizes the probabilities of high-reward tokens.",
    "Since these two objectives optimize in different directions, balancing them is critical for effective optimization.",
    "To achieve this balance, we use sequence-level gradient norms (Chen et al., 2018).",
    "Recall that the gradient of the DPO loss is:"
  ]
